stylometry: With this you are able to run many different simulations at once. You first have to figure out what order quantities you want to simualte within your problem. Then you can use @Risk and the risksimtable to run a simulation with 5 inputs. You have to set your iterations first and then you would run it with 5 inputs because you have 5 order quantities. As a result, you simualtions come up and show the max, min, mean, standard deviation , etc for each simulation. You want to pick the best fitted one which is the once that has a high mean, and a low profitability. There can be more than one solution, it depends on which one you think is best, but is should have a relatively low profitability and high mean.
